parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can lead to a lack of proper restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not work properly
the seat belt motor makes buzzing noises
the seat belt retractor locks up in the lock or unlock position
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt has incomplete retraction

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A tire blowout can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Water leakage through the sunroof can cause damage to the vehicle's interior, electrical systems, and upholstery, leading to costly repairs and potentially creating a safety hazard.
symptoms: Water spots or droplets on the interior roof
water accumulation on the floor or seats
rust or corrosion on surrounding metal components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A detached front bumper can cause damage to other vehicles or pedestrians, and may lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front bumper is loose or hanging
the front bumper falls off while driving
the front bumper is damaged or cracked
the vehicle's aerodynamics and stability are affected.
